{"nodes":[{"id":"concepts_cloud_run_conversion_backend_cloud_run_conversion_backend","label":"Cloud Run Conversion Backend","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\cloud-run-conversion-backend.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Planned or in-development backend service for HWP-to-PDF conversion. Referenced in root scripts as dev:api and build:api but may not be present in current workspace. Uses async job-based model processing."},{"id":"concepts_cloud_run_document_conversion_architecture_cloud_run_document_conversion_architecture","label":"Cloud Run Document Conversion Architecture","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\cloud-run-document-conversion-architecture.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Three-tier serverless architecture with Next.js frontend on Vercel, Cloud Run API/Worker for conversion, and GCS temp bucket. Offloads heavy conversion workloads from Vercel function limits (4.5MB/6MB payload)."},{"id":"concepts_documentation_gaps_documentation_gaps","label":"Documentation Gaps","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\documentation-gaps.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Missing root README.md, default Create Next App README in apps/web, and unverified root scripts (api, typecheck, test). Backend conversion service (apps/api) not found during init pass."},{"id":"concepts_gcs_lifecycle_management_gcs_lifecycle_management","label":"GCS Lifecycle Management","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\gcs-lifecycle-management.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Automatic cleanup of temporary files via GCS bucket lifecycle policies. Path-based rules target temp/original/ and temp/result/ prefixes for deletion after 1 day, plus AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload rule."},{"id":"concepts_gcs_lifecycle_rules_gcs_lifecycle_rules","label":"GCS Lifecycle Rules","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\gcs-lifecycle-rules.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Bucket-level policies in Google Cloud Storage for automatic object management via Delete, SetStorageClass, and AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload actions. Configuration in infrastructure/gcp/bucket-lifecycle.json."},{"id":"concepts_h2orestart_extension_h2orestart_extension","label":"H2Orestart Extension","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\h2orestart-extension.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Community LibreOffice extension (ebandal/H2Orestart, GPL-3.0, v0.7.12) that provides HWP v5.0 and HWPX support. Installed via unopkg add --shared, invoked with --infilter=Hwp2002_File. Required because built-in LibreOffice HWP filter has silent corruption bugs."},{"id":"concepts_hwp_file_format_conversion_challenges_hwp_file_format_conversion_challenges","label":"HWP File Format Conversion Challenges","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp-file-format-conversion-challenges.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"HWP is more complex than DOCX/PDF. LibreOffice built-in filter only supports v3.0 with v5.0 silent corruption (tdf#70097). H2Orestart community extension is the operational solution. High-risk: 30-60s cold start delays, OOM on large HWP files, cost leakage from incomplete multipart uploads."},{"id":"concepts_hwp_file_upload_constraints_hwp_file_upload_constraints","label":"HWP File Upload Constraints","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp-file-upload-constraints.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Centralized in packages/shared/src/index.ts. Only .hwp files accepted, max 20MB, async job/status response types, and polling constants. Single source of truth for upload validation."},{"id":"concepts_hwp_file_upload_validation_hwp_file_upload_validation","label":"HWP File Upload Validation","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp-file-upload-validation.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Validation logic for HWP uploads centralized in packages/shared/src/index.ts. Enforces .hwp extension and 20MB size limit, with async job/status response types and polling constants."},{"id":"concepts_hwp2pdf_project_hwp2pdf_project","label":"HWP2PDF Project","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp2pdf-project.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Serverless web service converting HWP to PDF. pnpm monorepo with Next.js frontend (apps/web) and Cloud Run backend. Async job-based workflow with LibreOffice headless conversion on Cloud Run."},{"id":"concepts_hwp2pdf_service_architecture_hwp2pdf_service_architecture","label":"HWP2PDF Service Architecture","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp2pdf-service-architecture.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Three-tier serverless cloud-native design: Next.js frontend on Vercel, Cloud Run API Gateway, GCS temp bucket, Cloud Run Converter Worker. Presigned URL direct uploads, UUID-based naming, Upstash Redis rate limiting, 2-second polling interval."},{"id":"concepts_hwp2pdfshared_package_hwp2pdfshared_package","label":"@hwp2pdf/shared Package","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\hwp2pdfshared-package.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Shared library at packages/shared, package name @hwp2pdf/shared, built with tsc. Centralizes .hwp file validation (20MB max), job status types, API routes, and polling constants for consistent use across frontend and backend."},{"id":"concepts_libreoffice_headless_conversion_libreoffice_headless_conversion","label":"LibreOffice Headless Conversion","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\libreoffice-headless-conversion.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"LibreOffice 7.6.x in headless mode transforms HWP to PDF on server. Uses H2Orestart filter (--infilter=Hwp2002_File), Korean locale (ko_KR.UTF-8), 2GiB memory min, 3-min timeout. Cold starts 60+s mitigated by listener mode (unoserver/Gotenberg)."},{"id":"concepts_llm_wiki_documentation_system_llm_wiki_documentation_system","label":"llm-wiki Documentation System","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\llm-wiki-documentation-system.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Repository-local documentation system for OpenCode sessions. Entry point docs/INDEX.md, with AGENTS.md for compact agent guidance, superpowers/specs/ for plans, docs/sessions/ for dated notes. Verified facts only."},{"id":"concepts_llm_wiki_repository_structure_llm_wiki_repository_structure","label":"llm-wiki Repository Structure","file_type":"concept","source_file":"C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\llm-wiki-repository-structure.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"pnpm monorepo with apps/* and packages/* globs. Root package.json specifies pnpm@8.15